Life is like a circus ride, full of ups and downs, twists and turns, and unexpected surprises. It can be thrilling and exciting, but also overwhelming and chaotic at times.
That's how I’m feeling right now. It’s a new year and all the expectations are there to overachieve- and I feel like I’m already failing. 
I know this is where my planner comes in. I’ve been using my @erincondren compact vertical to keep me going with the day to day- I think I’d be lost without it! But a planner isn't just a tool for organization. It can also be a source of inspiration and motivation. I want to get back to that part- the fun! And I will. I have to carve out the time and have some peace in the chaos. 

So if life feels like a circus ride for you too right now, remember that your planner has your back!  And it’s ok if you aren’t doing the MOST right now. Use your planners to do what you need in this moment. What’s your planner helping you do right now?!?

It’s National Handwriting Day! 🖊️✍️ If you are like me there are times when you don’t like your handwriting. I am learning to embrace it. I love seeing my parent’s handwriting, my kids, my friends…. It is immediately recognizable and feels like home. I try to remember that my writing does that for someone else. I think in this day of fancy lettering and perfection there is a lot of pressure. Just remember your writing is “you”. Your “signature”. Embrace it!

🎄🎅IT’S TIIIIMMMMEEE! I am posting my first @decemberdaily page! This isn’t the first one in the album, but the first one I created. I knew I wanted a story about my Christmas mug collections and I saw this paper and knew it was perfect! I created an oversized mug and made a tag that will tell the story. I made it brown and made little marshmallows to mimic cocoa. The mug folds out and will have pictures of all my mugs! 
I am so excited about this project and can’t wait to share more!!!

social_posts.post_text:
We had so much fun at the @atxlights Trail of Lights this year! This Austin tradition is a must do during the holiday season. And you have to end the night spinning under the Zilker Christmas tree!❤️🎄✨
Have you been to the Trail of Lights or is there something like it in your city? What’s your favorite holiday tradition? I think my favorite part was how much we laughed! 
#atx #austin  #trailoflights #trailoflightsaustin #christmaslights

So much can change in a year. 2023 was… a lot. It seems like Jan-March were SO LONG AGO, but Oct-Dec flew by. Does that make sense? This year was rough for so many reasons, but also great for so many more. I’m excited for what’s to come in 2024! Thanks for coming on this journey with me. ❤️

Hey! It’s my first scrapbook page of the year! I am so excited to get back to my scrapbook and memory planning roots this year and make documenting a priority again. For the @acherryontop_crafts January YouTube hop, the theme was “Try Something New”. I decided to use embroidery floss and some hand stitching on my page and I love the texture it added! 

Check out my video and the others in the YouTube hop for a chance to win a $25 gift certificate to ACOT! Are you memory keeping this year?
